import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between age and height?')

    return plt;

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['height'])
    plt.xticks([1], ['Height'])
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_height, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average height of people in the dataset?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    name_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the most common name in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
